added.title: The Copycats
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are confused when they meet Kiki and Quack, a pair of siblings that copy everything they do and say. Then they find out this copycat family is making money online from imitating the Watterson family! When they fail to encourage them to find their own identity, the Wattersons realize they need a more permanent solution.

added.title: The Fury
added.description: When an unknown figure shows up and insults their Mom, the kids are expecting a massive showdown but are surprised when Mom chooses the path of peace. Mom explains Yuki, Masami's mother, is an old school friend and repeatedly refuses to fight her, despite further provocation. However when Yuki threatens to get Mom fired from her job, Mom has no choice but to partake in a rematch of a karate match her and Yuki had fought as children.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Third
added.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

added.title: Know Your Fusion
added.description: Steven and the Gems delve deep into what makes a fusion so special.

added.title: Are You My Dad?
added.description: People are disappearing from Beach City, and Steven tries to solve the mystery.

added.title: It Could've Been Great
added.description: The Gems take a trip to the moon.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Tiger Millionaire
added.description: Steven joins Amethyst in an underground wrestling league.

added.title: Share and Share Dislike
added.description: Super Shooting Star Magisword is the coolest Magisword ever, but Vambre and Prohyas can't seem to share it, and even a quest to reclaim the never-melting ice cube back from Frosteratu can't shake their obsession.

added.title: Bad Man Oldman
added.description: When the Warriors re-thatch Old Man Oldman's roof and absentmindedly make it look like Prohyas' hair, Oldman dons an giant evil toupee exacts his revenge!

added.title: Witchy Simone Ruins Everything!
added.description: Witchy Simone joins Witch Way, but Gateaux is the odd cat out so he hires the Warriors to break up Witchy Simone and Morbidia and defeat a mission that has King Rexxtopher hopping mad!

added.title: Random Acts of Memory
added.description: The Warriors learn that Nohyas has been using a Selective Memory Magisword to erase select interactions with Prohyas' bizarre doppelganger their entire lives, so their new mission: take back that sword!

added.title: They See Me Trollblin
added.description: The tiny Kotassians hire the Warriors to exterminate two humongous Trollblins that have invaded their village, but it turns out that the Trollblins are actually nice guys and the Warriors switch sides to protect them in a Kotassiam/Trollblin War!

added.title: Party Re-Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to save Benson from an evil party company.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: The Unnaturals
added.description: Ben learns that evil robots have replaced all the kids at the Little League World Series. And now they want to replace the President of the USA!

added.title: Collateral Damage
added.description: Soundwave finally escapes the Shadow Zone to set up a Beacon Generator intended to summon Megatron! While the Bee Team engages the notorious Decepticon atop a skyscraper, Optimus Prime takes on Laserbeak in the skies over Crown City, and Sideswipe learns a lesson in considering the consequences of his actions.

added.title: Sick as a Bot
added.description: After the Energon seeking WINGCODE infects the Autobots with a virus, Bulkhead joins Grimlock in his frantic hunt for the Decepticon. But to capture the 'Con, the duo of brawny Bots has to learn to keep their cool and come up with a workable plan.

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When Optimus returns with old friends and dire warnings of a Cybertronian invasion of Earth, the Autobots must split up to defend their old home and their new one, with the Bee Team returning to Cybertron, while Optimus and his All-Stars stay behind to defend against the invasion's advanced force.

added.title: The Best VHS in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to return an overdue VHS to the store so they won't be banned from renting new movies.

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Party Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby look for help when their awesome house party turns lame.

added.title: To Cut a Woman's Hair
added.description: Finn needs to find a princess willing to give up a lock of her hair to save Jake from a balding witch.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
added.description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

added.title: Sugar, Spice, and Super Lice
added.description: When Buttercup gets super lice, her sisters must battle them to save her.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: Night of the Bat
added.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: Zombie King
added.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: The Witch's Garden
added.description: Jake loses his powers to a witch.

added.title: Arrested Development
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

added.title: Ben Again
added.description: When Eon causes 11-year old Ben swap minds with teen Ben, it's up to Gwen, Rook, and Professor Paradox to set things straight.  (Featuring Eon and Professor Paradox.)

added.title: Dungeon
added.description: Finn tries to conquer a dungeon without Jake's help.

added.title: Bubbles of the Opera
added.description: When Bubbles gets a bad school photo, it sends her into an existential tailspin of darkness.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Freak City
added.description: A magical man turns Finn into a foot. They meet others who have been similarly wronged and must work together.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: Chimney
added.description: While playing in the woods the boys befriend a wild dog, bring it home and name it Chimney. When the boys find themselves trapped in a well, the new pup is their only hope for escape.

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

removed.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

removed.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

removed.title: Catfight

removed.description: La manta de Pepper desaparece en una pijamada en la cabaña.

removed.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

removed.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.
